                    4 Ways a VDI Storage Solution Can Save (or Cost) Money
                














4 Ways a VDI Storage Solution Can Save (or Cost) Money





























An eBook from Citrix and Pure Storage
Many companies are now benefitting from the flexibility, mobility, and security that virtual desktop infrastructure (VDI) offers managing independent physical desktops.
But storage performance and cost remains an issue for VDI. Legacy systems, which rely on traditional spinning disks, fall short in adequately serving end-users. Even hybrid storage systems struggle to feed the voracious IO appetite of VDI systems.
It is possible to meet the demands of a VDI system while cutting both operational and deployment costs.
This eBook will discuss four ways to find savings in VDI storage — both by moving to an all-flash model and by finding the right flash solution.












